<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Quick Clarification (must read for Necros)</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Geiger">Geiger</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 1:46 p.m. 3/5/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Quick Clarification (must read for Necros)<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=2010" TARGET=_self>Question on Necromancers in pvp</A> (Ice)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I'm not sure if its fixed or not right now, but the other night the PVP server got a few tells about not using dot spells because people are losing exp when dying to them. I'm sorry to say I completely disagree with Verant, in what is a not so well thought out request. Necros only spells are basically dot spells. We have a lifetap spell and possibly a area affect spell, but our power is in our DOT spells, engulfing darkness (lvl 12), heat blood (lvl 12) and heart flutter (lvl 16). We get siphon life at 20 and Words of shadow (I think thats 20) Without DOT spells a necro is basically useless if attacked. THe pet also causes exp loss so are we to not use that as well? I pked someone the other day (right after the dot announcement) and my pet killed him. He lost XP and was furious. How can anyone reasonablly ask Necros to not use dot during PVP? It may be a rule, but what I'll do is use my dots and just make sure I siphon or tap him to death. I'm not running around the PVP server with no Guns.

<P>Anyone using them intentionally to make someone lose XP should be disciplined.
<P>Latez.
<P>&gt; Ok i have a question on Necromancers. I have a dark elf
<BR>&gt; Necromancer, just hit level 13, and i was fighting someone the
<BR>&gt; other night and i casted heat blood on them, well they gated off
<BR>&gt; and died. And they used the /tell command and told me they were
<BR>&gt; reporting me for using a Dot spell, and that they lost a level
<BR>&gt; because of the spell. Ok from what i see if this is true and im
<BR>&gt; not allowed to cast these spells, then what use is a
<BR>&gt; necromancer? These spells are the most damaging spells i have at
<BR>&gt; my disposal. I mean pets more or less suck now, that every,
<BR>&gt; "Tom, Dick and Harry", casts invisible on my pet, and
<BR>&gt; *Blamm*, its gone. So now im left with no pet, cloth armor, a
<BR>&gt; worn staff, and not being allowed to cast my best spells. So my
<BR>&gt; question's are A. Is casting invisible on my pet a bug, and do
<BR>&gt; they plan on fixing it? B. Are these Dot spells goin to be fixed
<BR>&gt; or, am i just not allowed to use them? I see no reason to play a
<BR>&gt; necromancer if A and B arent fixed, because i am more or less
<BR>&gt; playing a very weak spellcaster if thats the case.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
